<br>
Lots of guild members who are not officers or leaders of planar guilds don't know or understand what the KGC is or does. They do not understand the sacrifices needed by a guild leader or officer in order to track the rotations, keep on top of spawn times, check the boards two and three times daily, etc. They don't understand what good the KGC does them, because all they see is &quot;We have to wait until it's our turn for me to get my epic piece.&quot; <br>
<br>
For some, they accept what their guild leader says; after all, why follow someone whose word you don't believe? The KGC isn't just about telling you when you can and cannot hit a mob. It's about keeping peace on the server. It's about preventing Sol B from sounding like a pack of wolves at each other's throats every night. It's about people sublimating their natural desire to put themselves first for the greater good. Does that mean the individual sometimes is restricted in what he does? Damn right. Guess what, sunshine. That's what building a community is all about. <br>
<br>
/em gets on his soapbox<br>
<br>
See, these games aren't single-player games. They are massively multiplayer. They involve interaction with other people. Unlike Baldur's Gate, or Fallout, you can't just get what you want anytime you want it. You have to actually use social skills, you have to talk to people and you have to work with people. That's where the community comes in. Those who &quot;succeed&quot; the most in an MMOG are those who have some social skills, who are adept at working with others. It isn't just YOUR sandbox, or IC's sandbox. It's EVERYONE'S sandbox. And that means you don't always get to play with the dump truck when you want to play with it. In order to keep the sandbox from being ruled over by one bully, most of the organized groups on the server create the KGC to make sure that the largest percentage of the people using the sandbox can do so in an equal and fair way. Does that mean you can't play with the dump truck today? Yep, but, and here's the important part, YOUR DAY WILL COME. If you are patient. <br>
<br>
If you aren't patient, and want the dump truck NOW NOW NOW, you are just another little nutmuncher who cares for nothing but himself. <br>
<br>
Could the KGC use some work? Hell yes. Tracking rotations is part of the frustration and stress that led to my own burnout on EQ. But it's a damn sight better than getting KSed, trained, and otherwise run over by a guild whose members get home from work before I do, can stay up later than I can, and who don't give a shit about anyone but themselves. <p>Haemish MacLennan<br>
Founder<Br>
